events.name: Los Angeles Chargers vs. Minnesota Vikings
events.info: In accordance with California's and the venue's current health and safety guidelines, each person age 12 or older who attends a Chargers game agrees to provide proof (i) that the person has been fully vaccinated against COVID-19 (full vaccination means 14 days after the second shot of the Moderna or Pfizer vaccine or the single shot of the Johnson and Johnson vaccine); or (ii) of a negative COVID-19 test within 72 hours of the start time of the game. Each person who attends a game (except for children under the age of 2) will be required to wear a face mask that covers their mouth and nose at all times, except when actively eating or drinking. These requirements are subject to change and may be updated prior to the date of your game. Be sure to check back on this website closer to the date of your game for the latest requirements
